article.headline: Idaho St. 75, E. Washington 70
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- Amorrow Morgan scored 19 points and had eight assists and seven rebounds as Idaho State defeated Eastern Washington 75-70 on Saturday. Donnie Carson added 18 points for the Bengals (9-17, 6-6 Big Sky), Lucas Steijn had 15 and Chron Tatum had 10. Eastern Washington (11-15, 5-9) was led by Andy Genao with 21 points, Brandon Moore with 14, Bennie Valentine with 13 and Adris DeLeon with 10. Idaho State had its largest lead of 13 points with 10 minutes remaining. The closest Eastern Washington came after this was 74-70 with five seconds left. Idaho State had trailed by 8 points eight minutes into the game, but rallied to take a 39-30 lead at halftime. The Bengals shot 68 percent from the field in the first half, hitting 17 of 25 attempts.
